Do You Need to Pay Tax Monthly?
No, you donâ€™t need to pay tax monthly like an electricity bill. Hereâ€™s how it works for salaried persons like you:
________________________________________
1ï¸âƒ£ Salary Tax (TDS) â†’ Paid by Employer (Monthly)
â€¢	Your employer automatically deducts tax (TDS) every month from your salary.
â€¢	You donâ€™t need to do anything for this part.
ðŸ“Œ Example: If your annual taxable salary is â‚¹6L, your employer deducts TDS every month and pays it to the government.
________________________________________
2ï¸âƒ£ Extra Income Tax (Stocks, ETFs, FDs) â†’ You Need to Pay (If â‚¹10,000+ Tax)
If you earn extra income from Gold/Silver ETFs, Stocks, FDs, Freelance Work, etc., you need to check:
âœ… Small Profit (< â‚¹10,000 Tax)?
â†’ No need to pay monthly, just declare it while filing ITR (by July 31, 2025).
âœ… Big Profit (â‚¹10,000+ Tax)?
â†’ You must pay Advance Tax quarterly (every 3 months) to avoid penalties.
ðŸ“Œ Example:
â€¢	You make â‚¹50,000 profit from ETFs â†’ Tax = â‚¹7,500 (under 10K) â†’ Pay with ITR
â€¢	You make â‚¹2L profit from ETFs â†’ Tax = â‚¹30,000 â†’ Pay every 3 months
